<div class="card" style="position: absolute; left: 100px; top: 100px; height: 300px; width: 350px; align-items: center; border-radius: 20px;">
    <div style="position: absolute; background-color: darkgreen; height: 80px; width: 310px; margin-top: 5px; border-radius: 20px; text-align: center;">
        <h4 style="color: white; position: absolute; font-size: 17px; top: 22px; font-family: none;">Hey, notice how some icons are bigger than others?</h4>
        <h6 style="position: absolute; top: 90px; text-align: left;">That's because the bigger the icon, the more we're using of that thing. Big icons mean we need to think of ways to use less!</h6>
        <img src="~/d3-mainproject/icons-v2/water.png" style=" position: absolute; top: 200px; width: 70px; left: 20px;" />
        <img src="~/d3-mainproject/icons-v2/arrow.png" style="position: absolute; left: 60px; top: 180px" />
        <img src="~/d3-mainproject/icons-v2/water.png" style="position: absolute; width: 120px; top: 190px; right: 20px;" />
    </div>
    <div style="position: absolute; background-color: darkgreen; height: 100px; width: 330px; top: 370px; margin-top: 5px; border-radius: 20px; text-align: center;">
        <h4 style=" color: white; position: absolute; font-size: 17px; top: 22px; font-family: none;">By selecting them on the checkbox below, you can learn how we can all help!</h4>
    </div>
    </div>
    <div class="map-container">
        <iframe src="~/d3-mainproject/map.html" title="Map"></iframe>
    </div>
    <div style=" position: absolute; width: 250px; right: 90px; height: 750px; top: 80px;">
        <div style="position: absolute; top: 50px; height: 80px; width: 250px;">
            <img src="~/d3-mainproject/icons-v2/water.png" style="position: absolute; width: 100px" />
            <div style="position: absolute; top: 60px; left: 15px; width: 60px; background-color: darkgreen; text-align: center; border-radius: 5px">
                <h6 style="color: white; margin-top: 5px; font-size: 16px;">Water</h6>
            </div>
            <div style=" position: absolute; width: 170px; left: 80px; background-color: lightyellow;">
                <h4 style="font-family: none; font-size: 15px; color: black;margin-left:7px">
                    Water is essential for life. We need to use it wisely to keep our environment and ourselves healthy!
                </h4>
            </div>
        </div>
        <div style="position: absolute; top: 170px; height: 80px; width: 250px;">
            <img src="~/d3-mainproject/icons-v2/carbon.png" style="position: absolute; width: 100px" />
            <div style="position: absolute; top: 60px; left: 5px; width: 70px; background-color: darkgreen; text-align: center; border-radius: 5px">
                <h6 style="color: white; margin-top: 5px; font-size: 16px;">Green-house Gas</h6>
            </div>
            <div style=" position: absolute; width: 170px; top:15px; left: 80px; background-color: lightyellow;">
                <h4 style="font-family: none; font-size: 15px; color: black;margin-left:7px">
                    Greenhouse gases keep Earth warm, but too many can overheat our planet. It's important to produce less!
                </h4>
            </div>
        </div>
        <div style="position: absolute; top: 340px; height: 80px; width: 250px;">
            <img src="~/d3-mainproject/icons-v2/pm2_5.png" style="position: absolute; width: 100px" />
            <div style="position: absolute; top: 60px; left: 15px; width: 60px; background-color: darkgreen; text-align: center; border-radius: 5px">
                <h6 style="color: white; margin-top: 5px; font-size: 16px;">PM2.5</h6>
            </div>
            <div style=" position: absolute; width: 170px; left: 80px; background-color: lightyellow;">
                <h4 style="font-family: none; font-size: 15px; color: black;margin-left:7px">
                    PM2.5 is made of tiny particles that can harm our health. Clean air means less PM2.5!
                </h4>
            </div>
        </div>
        <div style="position: absolute; top: 460px; height: 80px; width: 250px;">
            <img src="~/d3-mainproject/icons-v2/non-renewable_energy.png" style="position: absolute; width: 100px" />
            <div style="position: absolute; top: 60px; left: -15px; width: 90px; background-color: darkgreen; text-align: center; border-radius: 5px">
                <h6 style="color: white; margin-top: 5px; font-size: 16px;">Non-renewable energy</h6>
            </div>
            <div style=" position: absolute; width: 170px; height:115px;left: 80px; background-color: lightyellow;margin-top:15px">
                <h4 style="font-family: none; font-size: 15px; color: black;margin-left:7px;">
                    Non-renewable energy like oil and coal is used up fast. We should try to use more sun and wind energy!
                </h4>
            </div>
        </div>
        <div style="position: absolute; top: 620px; height: 80px; width: 250px;">
            <img src="~/d3-mainproject/icons-v2/waste.png" style="position: absolute; width: 100px" />
            <div style="position: absolute; top: 60px; left: 15px; width: 60px; background-color: darkgreen; text-align: center; border-radius: 5px">
                <h6 style="color: white; margin-top: 5px; font-size: 16px;">Waste</h6>
            </div>
            <div style=" position: absolute; width: 170px; left: 80px; background-color: lightyellow; margin-top:10px">
                <h4 style="font-family: none; font-size: 15px; color: black;margin-left:7px;">
                    Waste should be small. Recycling helps our planet stay clean and green!
                </h4>
            </div>
        </div>


    </div>

    <script>
        function goToIndex() {
            window.location.href = "Dashboard";
        }
    </script>

    <script>
        var jsonData = @Html.Raw(Json.Encode(Model));
        sessionStorage.setItem('MapModelJson', JSON.stringify(jsonData));
    </script>
</body>
</html>